playwright (1.55.0-0ubuntu1~ppa1~noble1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Initial packaging of playwright 1.55.0 for the Avalan PPA.
  * Flipped from debian-rebuild to pypi-sdist: Debian sid's source
    carries the PEP 639 `license = "Apache-2.0"` form that Noble's
    setuptools rejects, and APT.md forbids Avalan-side patches on
    debian-rebuild rows. Upstream's PyPI distribution is wheels-only
    (each wheel bundles platform-specific browser drivers), so the
    sdist comes from the upstream GitHub tag instead.
  * Browsers are intentionally excluded -- callers install chromium
    (Recommends) or firefox via apt; Playwright's Python client
    drives whichever browser is on PATH at runtime.
  * Ship a quilt patch (pyproject-for-noble) that relaxes upstream's
    `setuptools==80.9.0`, `setuptools-scm==8.3.1`, `wheel==0.45.1`,
    `auditwheel==6.2.0` strict build-system pins to lower bounds
    Noble actually has, and rewrites `license = "Apache-2.0"` to
    the legacy `license = { text = "Apache-2.0" }` table form.

 -- Avalan Packaging Team <avalan@avalan.ai>  Mon, 18 May 2026 23:00:00 -0300
